<h1 id=3D"MandatorySwaggerSpecChecklist-SwaggerSpec-MandatoryChecklist">Swa=
gger Spec - Mandatory Checklist</h1><br>
<p>Note that the following checklist applies to both APIs built on the West=
pac Mesh platform as well as proxies for APIs delivered as part of third pa=
rty packages.&nbsp; Where specific items apply only to the former or the la=
tter then this is indicated for each specific item.</p>
<ul>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"b8042ac7-0545-48bf-94=
a0-fc1410b9f2b4">Info object</span> - modify all placeholder text from the =
template=20
<ul>
<li>version -- ensure that the version number is updated appropriately in l=
ine with the <a href=3D"https://semver.org/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D=
"nofollow">Semantic Versioning</a> principles&nbsp;</li>
<li>description -- <strong>Must</strong> clearly explain the purpose and sc=
ope of the API</li>
<li>x-goldenVersion -- Must ensure that the latest version of the golden te=
mplate used for writing the Spec</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><p>Host must be set to 'localhost:8080'</p></li>
<li><p>Base Path must conform to naming standards and be confirmed via API =
Naming Governance (usually before the Swagger spec is reviewed)</p></li>
<li><p>Schemes must be set to 'http'</p></li>
<li><p>Security must be of type: basic</p></li>
<li>The following items only apply to Westpac Mesh APIs (internal and partn=
er)=20
<ul>
<li>/healthcheck resource must be defined exactly as provided in the templa=
te</li>
</ul></li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"51135841-fa61-4566-af=
85-688881e19d9a">The following items only apply to Westpac Mesh internal AP=
Is</span>
<ul>
<li><p>All global header parameters prefixed with 'x-' which are marked as =
'required: true' must be included in all operations</p></li>
<li><p>brandSilo, when present, must be passed as either a query or body pa=
rameter, depending on the http verb being used. &nbsp;<span class=3D"inline=
-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"5037d51b-5e62-412b-8a3a-496ffffa0b30">Occasion=
ally</span>, it might be passed as a path parameter.</p></li>
<li>Only operations (verb+resource) approved by API Naming Governance <stro=
ng>must</strong> be used</li>
<li>Operation payload elements should be directly related to the resource</=
li>
<li>All responses must be wrapped inside '<strong>data</strong>' object.</l=
i>
<li>All operations <strong>must</strong> use appropriate HTTP response code=
s as defined in the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/d=
isplay/mesh/API+Detailed+Design+Standards" rel=3D"nofollow">Detailed Design=
 Guidelines</a> and exemplified in the&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(51,10=
2,255);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><a href=3D"https://bitbuck=
et.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse" class=3D"extern=
al-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Golden Swagger Template</a></span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,102,255);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0=
);">All error codes defined in the API must be documented as per the&nbsp;<=
a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contract=
s/browse" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Golden Swagger Template<=
/a></span><br></span></li>
<li>Abbreviations like ABN, ACN etc need to be exposed in capital letters</=
li>
<li>Appropriate <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/me=
sh/Common+Data+Types" rel=3D"nofollow">Common Data Types</a>&nbsp;are used =
where applicable</li>
<li>Date, time and timestamp fields must be declared as a string type and q=
ualified with the formats defined by the Swagger (OpenAPI) Specification.&n=
bsp;i.e.&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3339.txt" class=3D"ext=
ernal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">RFC3339</a> (an Internet profile of&nbsp;<a hr=
ef=3D"https://www.iso.org/iso-8601-date-and-time-format.html" class=3D"exte=
rnal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">ISO8601</a>)=20
<ul>
<li>date format - date (RFC3339 full-date)</li>
<li>timestamp format - date-time (RFC3339 date-time)</li>
<li>time (only) format - time (RFC3339 full-time) - this format is not pres=
cribed by the Swagger Specification but follows the intent of this specific=
ation<br><br></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Metadata Yaml File Checklist -&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MD/Metad=
ata+Yaml+files">Metadata Yaml files</a></strong></p>
<p>Component.yaml&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>brandSiloSupported -- Must identify which brand silos are explicitly su=
pported by the API</li>
<li>layer --Must correctly identify the layer applicable to this API</li>
<li>applicationId - Must identify and record the app Id from alfabet&nbsp;<=
/li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">previousVersion -&nbsp; If previous =
version is available then the previous version component name must be fille=
d.&nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">componentLifecycleState - Be default=
 this is approved. If the component deployed in production it should be upd=
ated to 'active' . If 'deprcated'&nbsp; then this should be updated.</span>=
</li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">tags - Add tags for quicker search i=
n <a href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"n=
ofollow">MESHConnect</a></span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Support.yaml </span></p>
<ul>
<li>supportTeam -- Must have Remedy support group name and application Id</=
li>
<li>vendor -- Must be provided where API is not hosted on (ie. a proxy for =
a third party API)</li>
<li>partner - Fill this section if this is a partner API</li>
</ul>
<p>Service-level.yaml&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>Under SLA ,record the maxTPS for your API</li>
<li>technicalDebt -- should be documented where applicable</li>
<li>detailedTechnicalDesignURL -- Must update with technical documentation =
(confluence etc)</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
